close_reason: "Implemented actionable lean JSON errors and public SDK error normalization primitives with zero SDK-boundary growth, docs, and full tests."
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/443\n\n## Problem\nThe structured error envelope carries two constant-prose fields on every error (`required`: \"Use values that match documented command constraints.\"; `why`: \"Validation protects data consistency...\"). They never vary by error and carry no actionable signal — pure token overhead in retry loops.\n\n## Proposed fix\nLean error mode (or simply omit constant `why`/`required` under --json unless error-specific): keep `code`, `detail`, `examples`, `next_steps`, `recovery.suggested_retry`. Verbose prose stays for human/TTY.\n\n## Definition of done\nJSON errors drop generic boilerplate (or --lean-errors/PM_LEAN_ERRORS added); error-envelope spec updated; agent docs note the mode. Related: pm-gdi7 covers unknown-option did-you-mean in the same envelope."
